                            <comment id="13603133" author="martykube" created="Fri, 15 Mar 2013 04:53:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch adds a command line option to generate JSON meta-data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch also improves the binary meta-data representation to include allowed values for enumerated types.  The improvement should be backwards compatibale as the additional data is tacked on at the end.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s worth considering dropping support for the binary format.  I&apos;m not sure who is using it...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615008" author="tdunning" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 08:02:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I factored large string constants out into resource files.  More review pending.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615016" author="tdunning" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 08:15:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another round of revision.  Cleaned up unused variables, indentation, extra file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615019" author="tdunning" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 08:17:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marty, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you like this, I can commit this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13616044" author="martykube" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2013 04:35:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, the changes look good to me.  Ship it!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, I did &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1163&quot; title=&quot;Make random forest classifier meta-data file human readable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-1163&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-1163&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; first.  I think they can go in any order.  But, best results will be from 63 and then 64.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These patches are all about getting the RF classifiers to read ARFF files without any monkey business. With 63 and 64 the integration and RF code will share a common JSON meta-data format.  We&apos;ll need one more patch to get RF to accept ARFF files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Longer term future steps are to get all classifiers to accept all format supported by the integration modules.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13679022" author="hudson" created="Sun, 9 Jun 2013 13:14:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #2062 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2062/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2062/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
